body:
To create a MongoDB Search index using the Atlas Administration API:

Send a `POST` request to the `search/indexes`
[endpoint](api/doc/atlas-admin-api-v2/operation/operation-creategroupclustersearchindex).

> **Note:** This `curl` command uses a service account access token ([OAuth 2.0](https://oauth.net/2/)) to authenticate
> instead of API keys. To learn more, see [API Access Lists endpoint](atlas-admin-api-access).

```sh
curl --header "Authorization: Bearer {ACCESS-TOKEN}" \
  --header "Accept: application/json" \
  --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
  --include \
  --request POST "https://cloud.mongodb.com/api/atlas/v2/groups/{groupId}/clusters/{clusterName}/search/indexes" \
  --data '
       {
       "collectionName": "<collection-name>",
       "database": "<database-name>",
       "name": "<index-name>",
       "type": "search",
       "definition":
       {
           "analyzer": "<analyzer-name>",
           "searchAnalyzer": "<analyzer-name>",
           "mappings": {
           "dynamic": <boolean>,
           "fields": { <field-definition> }
           },
           "numPartitions": <integer>,
           "analyzers": [ {
               <custom-analyzer-definition>
           }
           ],
           "storedSource": <boolean> | {
           <stored-source-definition>
           },
           "synonyms": [
           {
               <synonym-mapping-definition>
           }
           ]
       }
     }'
```

To learn more about the syntax and parameters for this
endpoint, see [Create One](api/doc/atlas-admin-api-v2/operation/operation-creategroupclustersearchindex).

IMPORTANT: Atlas doesn't create the index if the collection
doesn't exist, but it still returns a `200` status.
